list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a place on the coast where vessels may find shelter, especially one protected from rough water by piers, jetties, and other artificial structures.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: they enjoyed fishing in the harbor
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Họ thích câu cá trong bến cảng

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: keep (a thought or feeling, typically a negative one) in one's mind, especially secretly.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: she started to harbor doubts about the wisdom of their journey
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Cô bắt đầu hùn nghi ngờ về trí tuệ của hành trình của họ

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: shelter or hide (a criminal or wanted person).
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he was suspected of harboring an escaped prisoner
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Ông bị nghi ngờ chứa chấp một tù nhân trốn thoát

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a ship or its crew) moor in a harbor.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: he might have harbored in San Francisco
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Anh ta có thể đã chứa chấp ở San Francisco
